<cell id="title-14"><cell_type>markdown</cell_type># Chapter 14 — LoRA Fine-tuning</cell id="title-14">
<cell id="intro-14"><cell_type>markdown</cell_type>A pre-trained model is like a brilliant student who read the internet but never learned to converse. Supervised Fine-Tuning (SFT) teaches it to follow instructions and become a helpful assistant — the transformation from text predictor to AI chatbot.</cell id="intro-14">
<cell id="code-14">import torch
import torch.nn as nn

print("=== LoRA (Low-Rank Adaptation) from Scratch ===\n")

d_model = 4096
rank = 16
lora_alpha = 32
scaling = lora_alpha / rank

torch.manual_seed(42)
W = nn.Linear(d_model, d_model, bias=False)
W.weight.requires_grad_(False)

A = nn.Linear(d_model, rank, bias=False)
B = nn.Linear(rank, d_model, bias=False)
nn.init.zeros_(B.weight)

base_params = d_model * d_model
lora_params = 2 * d_model * rank
print(f"Base W:   {base_params:>12,} params (frozen)")
print(f"LoRA A+B: {lora_params:>12,} params (trainable)")
print(f"Ratio:    {lora_params/base_params*100:.2f}%")

x = torch.randn(2, 10, d_model)
with torch.no_grad():
    base_out = W(x)
    lora_out = W(x) + scaling * B(A(x))
print(f"\nDiff at init (B=0): {(base_out - lora_out).abs().mean():.6f}")

out = W(x) + scaling * B(A(x))
loss = out.sum()
loss.backward()
print(f"\nW.weight.grad:      {W.weight.grad}")
print(f"A.weight.grad norm: {A.weight.grad.norm():.4f}")
print(f"B.weight.grad norm: {B.weight.grad.norm():.4f}")</cell id="code-14">
<cell id="code-14-prod">from peft import LoraConfig, get_peft_model
from trl import SFTTrainer, SFTConfig

lora_config = LoraConfig(
    r=16, lora_alpha=32, lora_dropout=0.05,
    target_modules=["q_proj", "k_proj", "v_proj", "o_proj"],
)
model = get_peft_model(base_model, lora_config)
# trainable: 4M / 6.7B total = 0.06%

